cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC. 

The paper is about a GUI tool for designing and training deep learning frameworks, specifically Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since CNNs are commonly used in image processing tasks. The paper also mentions performing experiments and analyzing results, which suggests it could also fit into cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the mention of a user-friendly interface and design with extensibility in mind suggests a potential fit for cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
